d 'I_INEQ': module to provide individual decomposition of inequality measures
d
d	i_ineq computes individual components of three inequality
d measures (Gini index, Theil's L, and Theil's T)    and their
d group-based decompositions.  The function takes as input an
d outcome variable (such as income), a	  grouping variable, and an
d optional sampling weight. It returns three new variables
d containing individual    contributions and their between-group
d and within-group components.	  The Gini index (or Gini
d coefficient) is a widely used measure of inequality that ranges
d from 0 (perfect    equality) to 1 (maximum inequality). Theil's L
d (also known as Theil's second measure or mean log deviation)	 
d and Theil's T (also known as Theil's first measure or Theil
d entropy index) are members of the generalized    entropy family
d of inequality measures.    This command implements the individual
d decomposition methods described in Liao (Sociological Methods &
d Research, 2022), which allow	  researchers to examine the
d contribution of each individual to overall inequality and to
d decompose these    contributions into between-group and
d within-group components. 
d
d KW: inequality
d KW: Gini
d KW: Theil's L
d KW: Theil's T
d
d Requires: Stata version 14
d
d Distribution-Date: 20251116
d
d Author: Tim Liao, University of Illinois
d Support: email  tfliao@@illinois.edu
d
f i_ineq.ado
f i_ineq.sthlp
